# Http Transport for the M1cro Framework

# Disclaimer

This project is far from finished and API can change at any time.
So, don't use in anything important!


# Introduction

This is the Http transport for the M1cro Framework.
For more information see the homepage of that project at <https://github.com/Lerint/m1cro>.


# Installation

    npm install m1cro-transport-http


# Example usage

    var m1cro = require('m1cro');
    var m1croHttp = require('m1cro-transport-http');

    // default options
    var transportOptions = {
        host: 'localhost',
        port: 1971
    };
    var transportHttp =  new m1croHttp.Transport(transportOptions);

    var iface = new m1cro.interface({transport: transportHttp});
    iface.on('start', ..... )


# Creating a new Transport instance

    var transportHttp =  new TransportHttp(options);

### options

- `connect` object with the following properties
These options can also be set using the listed environment variables.

    - `host` hostname of HTTP server, environment: `M1CRO_HTTP_HOST`, default: 'localhost'
    - `port` port to connect to, environment: `M1CRO_HTTP_PORT`, default: '5672'
    - `username` username to connect with, environment: `M1CRO_HTTP_USERNAME`, default 'guest'
    - `password` password to connect with, environment: `M1CRO_HTTP_LOGIN`, default 'guest',
